This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.3.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/www/hacking.html for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.3.0:
================

Candidate changes:

 * r17039, r17051
   Fix issue 767: Commit uses temporary file in current directory.
   Remark:
     Commits in read-only directories therefore fail.  This revision adds
     graceful fallback.
   Votes:
     +1: dionisos, rooneg

Approved changes:

 * r17093, r17095
   Avoid usage of $< in SWIG header wrapper generator rules.
   Justification:
     Necessary for compatibility with BSD make.
   Votes:
     +1: djames, danderson, lundblad

